The "Peace Relief-2021" Joint Exercise of the Chinese and Vietnamese Military has successfully ended- Xinhua News
On the morning of December 12, the Chinese participating delegation of the "Peace Relief-2021" Joint Exercise of the Chinese and Vietnamese Military returned safely to the Guangxi region of China, marking the successful completion of the 7-day training mission.
During this joint exercise, the Chinese and Vietnamese military focused on the important issue of humanitarian medical rescue, closely following the mission of saving lives and caring for the injured. The exercise completed joint medical command, joint on-site rescue, and bulk treatment of casualties in accordance with realistic standards, effectively enhancing the medical security capabilities of the two armies.
The results of the exercise have been recognized by both the Chinese and Vietnamese military.
Ruan Xiongsheng, head of the Vietnamese exercise directing committee and vice chief of staff and chief of logistics of the Vietnamese People's Army, said at the conclusion ceremony of the exercise that Vietnamese army medical personnel learned about exercise organization and professional activities from their Chinese counterparts and also learned about China's medical and security equipment.
The results achieved in the exercise demonstrate the professional ability of the two countries' military medical forces in medical assistance and epidemic prevention and control.
Chen Chunming, the head of the Chinese guidance and coordination group and the deputy head of the Health Bureau of the Logistics Support Department of the Central Military Commission, stated that this exercise is another innovative practice that builds on the successful joint medical examination activity held in 2018 and has a very important milestone significance.
During the exercise, the Chinese People's Liberation Army donated medical protective masks, protective clothing, and rapid nucleic acid detection equipment and other health and epidemic prevention materials to the Vietnamese People's Army.